    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my ac unit outside is making a loud humming noise but the fan isnt actually spinning. any idea what's wrong and is it safe to go look at it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A loud humming noise with the fan not spinning often indicates an electrical issue or a failed motor in your AC unit. It could be an issue with the capacitor, which starts the motor, or the motor itself may be seized. While it's best not to open up electrical components yourself, safely observing the exterior unit is generally safe; however, if the humming is accompanied by strong sparks or burning smells, stay away immediately and call a professional.",
