    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "could it be the capacitor? i heard someone say that's usually the culprit when it hums but wont start up. also what should i look for if i do decide to open the panel and check it myself?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, the capacitor is a very common culprit for humming without the fan spinning, as it provides the necessary jolt to get the motor going. If you decide to check the panel, look specifically for the capacitor; you can often check its rating and see if it feels warm or swollen. Be extremely cautious, as capacitors store a dangerous electrical charge even when the unit is off, so ensure the power to the unit is completely shut off at the breaker before touching anything.",
      "source": "target",
