      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's perfectly understandable to be nervous about electrical issues, so consulting a professional is highly recommended. Beyond the capacitor, failed motor windings or a tripped overload protector can also cause the humming without rotation. Sometimes, a simple blockage or excessive dirt buildup on the coils can create enough resistance to mimic an electrical failure. Given the potential for hazards, having an HVAC technician diagnose it is the safest step.",
